{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-03",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_03_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "03 - A Caucus-race and a Long Tale",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 1.54,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 255.1,
  "page_end_sec": 495.2,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 255.1,
      "end": 256.38,
      "text": "And they all crowded round it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.4,
      "end": 257.3,
      "text": "panting, and asking,"
    },
    {
      "start": 257.46,
      "end": 258.36,
      "text": "\"But who has won?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 259.44,
      "end": 260.82,
      "text": "This question the Dodo could not",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 260.82,
      "end": 262.56,
      "text": "answer without a great deal of thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.7,
      "end": 264.0,
      "text": "and it stood for a long"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.16,
      "end": 266.26,
      "text": "time with one finger pressed upon its forehead"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.76,
      "end": 268.88,
      "text": "(the position in which you usually see Shakespeare,"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.88,
      "end": 270.02,
      "text": "in the pictures of him),"
    },
    {
      "start": 270.94,
      "end": 272.44,
      "text": "while the rest waited in silence."
    },
    {
      "start": 272.69,
      "end": 274.38,
      "text": "At last the Dodo said"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.22,
      "end": 276.1,
      "text": "\"_Everybody_ has won,"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.3,
      "end": 277.88,
      "text": "and _all_ must have prizes.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 279.45,
      "end": 281.06,
      "text": "\"But who is to give the prizes?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 281.26,
      "end": 282.9,
      "text": "quite a chorus of voices asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.08,
      "end": 284.38,
      "text": "\"Why,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.46,
      "end": 284.66,
      "text": "_she_,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.84,
      "end": 285.3,
      "text": "of course,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 285.5,
      "end": 286.36,
      "text": "said the Dodo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.4,
      "end": 288.04,
      "text": "pointing to Alice with one finger;"
    },
    {
      "start": 288.12,
      "end": 289.08,
      "text": "and the whole party"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.26,
      "end": 290.52,
      "text": "at once crowded round her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.68,
      "end": 292.18,
      "text": "calling out in a confused way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.72,
      "end": 293.08,
      "text": "\"Prizes!"
    },
    {
      "start": 293.24,
      "end": 293.92,
      "text": "Prizes!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 295.46,
      "end": 297.08,
      "text": "Alice had no idea what to do,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.2,
      "end": 300.06,
      "text": "and in despair she put her hand in her pocket, and pulled"
    },
    {
      "start": 300.06,
      "end": 301.24,
      "text": "out a box of comfits"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.36,
      "end": 303.86,
      "text": "(luckily the salt water had not got into it),"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.9,
      "end": 305.02,
      "text": "and handed them round"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.02,
      "end": 305.5,
      "text": "as prizes."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.76,
      "end": 308.06,
      "text": "There was exactly one apiece all round."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.5,
      "end": 310.88,
      "text": "\"But she must have a prize herself,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 310.98,
      "end": 311.34,
      "text": "you know,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 311.5,
      "end": 312.34,
      "text": "said the Mouse."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.376,
      "end": 313.8,
      "text": "\"Of course,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 314.3,
      "end": 316.06,
      "text": "the Dodo replied very gravely."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.75,
      "end": 319.14,
      "text": "\"What else have you got in your pocket?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 319.44,
      "end": 320.96,
      "text": "it went on, turning to Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.888,
      "end": 322.56,
      "text": "\"Only a thimble,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 322.68,
      "end": 323.58,
      "text": "said Alice sadly."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.06,
      "end": 324.8,
      "text": "\"Hand it over here,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 325.02,
      "end": 325.74,
      "text": "said the Dodo."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.62,
      "end": 329.46,
      "text": "Then they all crowded round her once more,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 329.64,
      "end": 332.38,
      "text": "while the Dodo solemnly presented the thimble,"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.46,
      "end": 332.72,
      "text": "saying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 333.28,
      "end": 336.58,
      "text": "\"We beg your acceptance of this elegant thimble;\""
    },
    {
      "start": 337.1,
      "end": 338.94,
      "text": "and, when it had finished this short speech,"
    },
    {
      "start": 339.1,
      "end": 339.82,
      "text": "they all cheered."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.8,
      "end": 342.57,
      "text": "Alice thought the whole thing very absurd,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 342.68,
      "end": 345.48,
      "text": "but they all looked so grave that she did not dare to laugh;"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.02,
      "end": 348.1,
      "text": "and, as she could not think of anything to say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.7,
      "end": 350.54,
      "text": "she simply bowed, and took the thimble,"
    },
    {
      "start": 350.66,
      "end": 352.3,
      "text": "looking as solemn as she could."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.65,
      "end": 355.86,
      "text": "The next thing was to eat the comfits;",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 356.38,
      "end": 357.96,
      "text": "this caused some noise and confusion,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.24,
      "end": 360.98,
      "text": "as the large birds complained that they could not taste theirs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.44,
      "end": 363.86,
      "text": "and the small ones choked and had to be patted on the back."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.5,
      "end": 364.8,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.98,
      "end": 366.26,
      "text": "it was over at last,"
    },
    {
      "start": 366.38,
      "end": 368.08,
      "text": "and they sat down again in a ring,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.26,
      "end": 370.18,
      "text": "and begged the Mouse to tell them something more."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.34,
      "end": 372.72,
      "text": "\"You promised to tell me your history,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 372.84,
      "end": 373.14,
      "text": "you know,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 373.24,
      "end": 373.66,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.48,
      "end": 377.27,
      "text": "\"and why it is you hate--C and D,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 377.62,
      "end": 378.96,
      "text": "she added in a whisper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.16,
      "end": 380.92,
      "text": "half afraid that it would be offended again."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.94,
      "end": 383.48,
      "text": "\"Mine is a long and sad tale!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 383.72,
      "end": 384.3,
      "text": "said the Mouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 384.42,
      "end": 385.82,
      "text": "turning to Alice and sighing."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.72,
      "end": 387.6,
      "text": "\"It _is_ a long tail,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 387.62,
      "end": 387.96,
      "text": "certainly,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 388.18,
      "end": 388.74,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 388.9,
      "end": 391.0,
      "text": "looking down with wonder at the Mouse's tail;"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.78,
      "end": 392.92,
      "text": "\"but why do you call it sad?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 393.76,
      "end": 396.46,
      "text": "And she kept on puzzling about it while the Mouse was speaking,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.7,
      "end": 399.68,
      "text": "so that her idea of the tale was something like this:--"
    },
    {
      "start": 401.632,
      "end": 404.76,
      "text": "\"Fury said to a mouse, That he met in the house,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 404.92,
      "end": 406.4,
      "text": "'Let us both go to law:"
    },
    {
      "start": 406.98,
      "end": 408.06,
      "text": "_I_ will prose-cute _you_.--"
    },
    {
      "start": 409.14,
      "end": 409.84,
      "text": "Come,"
    },
    {
      "start": 410.02,
      "end": 411.2,
      "text": "I'll take no de-nial:"
    },
    {
      "start": 411.36,
      "end": 412.56,
      "text": "We must have the trial;"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.12,
      "end": 415.4,
      "text": "For really this morn-ing I've nothing to do.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 416.2,
      "end": 417.5,
      "text": "Said the mouse to the cur,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.72,
      "end": 418.86,
      "text": "'Such a trial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.0,
      "end": 419.52,
      "text": "dear sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.66,
      "end": 421.18,
      "text": "With no jury or judge,"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.34,
      "end": 422.8,
      "text": "would be wast-ing our breath.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.288,
      "end": 424.84,
      "text": "'I'll be judge,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.98,
      "end": 425.7,
      "text": "I'll be jury,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.88,
      "end": 427.32,
      "text": "said cun-ning old Fury:"
    },
    {
      "start": 428.08,
      "end": 430.7,
      "text": "'I'll try the whole cause, and con-demn you to death.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.8,
      "end": 432.4,
      "text": "\"You are not attending!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 432.8,
      "end": 434.4,
      "text": "said the Mouse to Alice severely."
    },
    {
      "start": 435.5,
      "end": 436.4,
      "text": "\"What are you thinking of?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 437.56,
      "end": 438.94,
      "text": "\"I beg your pardon,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 439.06,
      "end": 440.26,
      "text": "said Alice very humbly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.32,
      "end": 441.76,
      "text": "\"you had got to the fifth bend,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.92,
      "end": 442.24,
      "text": "I think?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 442.74,
      "end": 443.3,
      "text": "\"I had _not_!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 443.58,
      "end": 444.89,
      "text": "cried the Mouse, angrily."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.64,
      "end": 445.9,
      "text": "\"A knot!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 446.1,
      "end": 446.66,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 446.78,
      "end": 448.52,
      "text": "always ready to make herself useful,"
    },
    {
      "start": 448.9,
      "end": 450.42,
      "text": "and looking anxiously about her."
    },
    {
      "start": 451.08,
      "end": 451.28,
      "text": "\"Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.34,
      "end": 452.86,
      "text": "do let me help to undo it!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 454.14,
      "end": 456.28,
      "text": "\"I shall do nothing of the sort,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 456.44,
      "end": 457.68,
      "text": "said the Mouse, getting up and walking away."
    },
    {
      "start": 458.28,
      "end": 460.49,
      "text": "\"You insult me by talking such nonsense!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 461.64,
      "end": 463.48,
      "text": "\"I didn't mean it!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 463.84,
      "end": 465.02,
      "text": "pleaded poor Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 465.22,
      "end": 465.85,
      "text": "\"But you're so easily offended,"
    },
    {
      "start": 465.85,
      "end": 466.2,
      "text": "you know!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 466.68,
      "end": 468.82,
      "text": "The Mouse only growled in reply.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 470.432,
      "end": 473.5,
      "text": "\"Please come back and finish your story!\" Alice called after it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 473.88,
      "end": 475.68,
      "text": "and the others all joined in chorus,"
    },
    {
      "start": 476.02,
      "end": 476.16,
      "text": "\"Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 476.18,
      "end": 477.0,
      "text": "please do!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 477.56,
      "end": 479.06,
      "text": "but the Mouse only shook its head"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.25,
      "end": 481.02,
      "text": "impatiently and walked a little quicker."
    },
    {
      "start": 483.0,
      "end": 484.34,
      "text": "\"What a pity it wouldn't stay!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 484.74,
      "end": 485.5,
      "text": "sighed the Lory,"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.64,
      "end": 487.22,
      "text": "as soon as it was quite out of sight;"
    },
    {
      "start": 487.34,
      "end": 490.5,
      "text": "and an old Crab took the opportunity of saying to her daughter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.82,
      "end": 490.92,
      "text": "\"Ah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 491.48,
      "end": 491.9,
      "text": "my dear!"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.08,
      "end": 495.2,
      "text": "Let this be a lesson to you never to lose _your_ temper!\""
    }
  ]
}